This is an old question, so historical figures such as Charlemagne, Shakespeare have their own opinion on this question. These days, scientific data has emerged that can answer this question. For example, Aboriginal people, who use compass points to indicate direction, have a very keen sense of direction and they have a unique culture. Moreover, the number of words that indicate numbers and colors is also influence the speaker’s thinking. Spanish and German are also affected that their nouns have gender, so the way that they are described same noun is different.
